sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Application
    participant Browser as User's Browser
    participant Auth as Authorization Server

    Note over App: 1. Generate code_verifier (random)
    App->>App: code_verifier = randomBytes(32)
    App->>App: code_challenge = SHA256(code_verifier)
    App->>App: state = randomBytes(32)

    Note over App: 2. Start localhost server on port N
    App->>App: server.listen(N)

    Note over App: 3. Redirect user to authorize
    App->>Browser: GET /oauth/authorize?<br/>client_id=...<br/>redirect_uri=http://localhost:N/callback<br/>response_type=code<br/>scope=user:inference user:profile<br/>code_challenge={code_challenge}<br/>code_challenge_method=S256<br/>state={state}

    Browser->>Auth: Authorization request

    Note over Browser: 4. User logs in & approves
    Auth->>Browser: Authorization screen

    Note over Auth: 5. Server stores code_challenge<br/>mapped to this session

    Note over Browser: 6. Redirect with authorization code
    Auth->>Browser: 302 http://localhost:N/callback?<br/>code=AUTH_CODE<br/>state={state}

    Note over Browser: 7. Browser redirects to localhost
    Browser->>App: GET /callback?code=AUTH_CODE&state={state}

    Note over App: 8. Validate state matches
    App->>App: if (state != expected_state) reject()

    Note over App: 9. Exchange code for tokens
    App->>Auth: POST /oauth/token<br/>{<br/>  "grant_type": "authorization_code",<br/>  "code": "AUTH_CODE",<br/>  "redirect_uri": "http://localhost:N/callback",<br/>  "client_id": "...",<br/>  "code_verifier": "{code_verifier}",<br/>  "state": "{state}"<br/>}

    Note over Auth: 10. Verify PKCE challenge
    Auth->>Auth: hash = SHA256(code_verifier)<br/>if (hash != code_challenge) reject()

    Note over Auth: 11. Issue tokens
    Auth-->>App: {<br/>  "access_token": "...",<br/>  "refresh_token": "...",<br/>  "expires_in": 3600,<br/>  "scope": "user:inference user:profile"<br/>}

    Note over App: 12. Store tokens securely
